If you are convinced that the person has attitude issue, it is always better for the organisation to part with such employees. However, to be fair to this person in this specific case, the matter may be approached as below;
- you may share specifics of your concern or dissatisfaction highlighting clearly wherever you feel a better attitude from her could have resolved the matters. Then to let her know that still you would like to give her a fair chance and in that aspect you would like her to propose 1-3 key impact projects / assignments in her domain which she is confident of implementing within a given time suitable as per her. However if she fails to deliver, you would be left with no other option but to part as good friend. 
The benefit of this approach is if she succeeds you would have a reformed person with experience while if she fails you can actually terminate her where she knows you gave her a good last chance!
